summary: Create Tulparas Java application and maven plugin to cover all automation phases
description:
Tulparas (short for Tulpar Automation System) is a Java application that manages and executes all automation phases for Tulpar; build, deployment, application and environment verification tests, cluster provisioning and performance testing. It will reside on the management host, which we use as our automation server for Tulpar, as a service; and it will serve via its exposed REST interfaces. It will also have a maven plugin, which will be used on the client side (by Tulpar developers) to interface with Tulparas in a structured way.

It will consist of the following maven modules, whose details are covered in more detail here: https://confluence.critical-factor.com/display/~ysapli/Tulparas
- tulparas-api
- tulparas-server
- tulparas-persistence
- tulparas-ssh
- tulparas-plugin

issues.summary: Fix the ethernet port instability in a compiled u-boot
issues.description: The u-boot compiled using custom config is very unstable in downloading something using tftp or dhcp commands. Even ping is unstable. In my case i used parallella.h file from official parallella-uboot git repository. Needed to define the correct configs to make a true Giga ethernet connection :)
